      <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="census"></a>Census 2021 - Sunday 21 March</h3>
      <p>The census is coming. By taking part, you can help to inform decisions on services that shape your community, such as schools, doctors’ surgeries and bike lanes. It’s important you fill in your census questionnaire because the information you share affects the life of every single person living in England and Wales. Because these things matter to us all, everyone needs to complete the census. Do not worry, your information is protected by law. That means government officials dealing with payments or services you receive cannot see it.</p>
      <p>Census Day is Sunday 21 March. You can fill yours in online as soon as you get your access code in the post. If your household circumstances change on Census Day, you can let The Office for National Statistics (ONS) know.</p>
      <p>If you need help, you can visit www.census.gov.uk where there’s a wide range of support services available. There will also be help by phone to fill in your Census and if you need a paper copy they will be available by requesting one through the Contact Centre (the number will be in your letter).</p>
      <p><%= link_to "More information here", "resource/census21.pdf" %></p>


      <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="trains"></a>Train Service alterations</h3>
      <p>From Govia Thameslink Railway – Train Service Alterations from 22 February 2021</p>
      <p>Train services are being reduced to better match anticipated demand in the months ahead, and to ensure services are as reliable as possible at a time when colleagues may need to self-isolate or shield.</p>
      <p>The plan focuses on maintaining services earlier in the morning, later in the evening and at peak times, based on feedback from key workers and stakeholders. Train services will change across the network, so as always, it is important that customers check journeys at <%= link_to "www.nationalrail.co.uk", "http://www.nationalrail.co.uk" %> before travelling.</p>
      <p>A summary of the main changes from 22 February affecting Sanderstead:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>East Grinstead and London Victoria. The Southern service will operate as hourly throughout the day, with a half-hourly service to support peak time and school travel.</li>
        <li>Sanderstead passengers may consider alternative services from Purley Oaks station [0.3 miles]</li>
        <li>East Grinstead and Bedford. The peak-time-only Thameslink service from East Grinstead to Bedford will not operate.</li>
        <li>Purley Oaks and London Bridge. A reduced service will be provided at Purley Oaks and South Croydon. Purley Oaks passengers may wish to consider alternative services from Sanderstead station (0.3 miles).</li>
      </ul>

