      <h3><a class="anchor" id="top" name="malcolm"></a>A tribute to Malcolm Saunders</h3>
      <p>It is with much regret that the SRA Committee have to inform you that a valued member of our executive passed away recently. Malcom Saunders joined the committee in 1995 for nine years and later re-joined in 2018. He quietly and efficiently assisted in many tasks. He will be sorely missed.</p>
      <p>Most recently Malcolm was a key person in our involvement with the DEMOC campaign and for many years has been involved with the Neighbourwood Watch. He was also a judge for our ‘Hear Me Speak’ competition for local schoolchildren.</p>
      <p>Malcolm was the key person in the Sandestead Millenium project in Sanderstead as he had the idea and vision to do something for Sanderstead to mark this occasion. As early as 1996 a public meeting was held and a committee formed. You only have to look around Sanderstead to see what was achieved: in the recreation ground the multi games court and children’s cycling track; the restored Sanderstead sign by the roundabout; the floodlighting of All Saints; Church; and local schoolchildren were given a commemorative mug.</p>
      <p>Malcolm was involved with many other committees and organisations giving his time to help the local community. When his eldest son was a cub he became involved with 16 th Purley Scout Group as transport officer looking after the scout van and he later became Fundraising Chairman in which capacity he organised several Gruffy Fayres, jumble sales, barn dances and old folks suppers.</p>
      <p>Our thoughts are with his family at this time.</p>


